bilingual.source: She has an inborn ability to lead.
bilingual.target: 她有一种先天的领导能力。

bilingual.source: She was appointed to lead the new project.
bilingual.target: 她被任命领导这个新项目。

bilingual.source: They deputed John to lead the new project.
bilingual.target: 他们委派约翰领导新项目。

bilingual.source: This project needs an old hand to lead.
bilingual.target: 这个项目需要一个老手来领导。

bilingual.source: She has the competency to lead the team effectively.
Lead and "lead" are examples of homographs in English.
bilingual.target: “Lead（铅）”和“lead（领导）”是英语中的同形异义词。

bilingual.source: This project needs a practised hand to lead it.
bilingual.target: 这个项目需要一个熟手来领导。

bilingual.source: They chose a new head to lead the company.
bilingual.target: 他们选了一个新的水头来领导公司。

list.abstract: lead，英文单词，作名词、动词等，翻译为领导、致使、指挥、铅、导线、榜样等。
lead，一支由四个日本男孩所组成的乐队名称，为当红偶像团体w-inds.的同门师弟。主要作品有発売真夏のMagic 、発売 "Show me the way" 等等。 2020年2月14日，发行合唱单曲《超展开》。

yingyinNormal.en: This is an effort that America has the unique ability to lead.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是美国完全有能力领导的行动。

yingyinNormal.en: Pardon me for asking, but without a princess, who's gonna lead us?
yingyinNormal.zh: 嗯，冒昧问一句，没有公主，谁将领导我们呢?

yingyinNormal.en: A great man doesn't seek to lead. He is called to it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 伟大之人不是主动去成为领导者的。他是受到召唤而有所响应。

yingyinNormal.en: So the United States will continue to help lead the global response in West Africa.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因此，美国将继续领导在西非的全球性努力。

yingyinNormal.en: And we'll lead a broad coalition of nations who have a stake in this fight.
yingyinNormal.zh: 同时我们将领导各利益相关国形成广泛同盟共同打击恐怖分子。

yingyinNormal.en: How'd you like to lead your own army? Dragon Army. Sir, I've never heard of a Dragon Army.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你自己领导一个战队怎么样？飞龙战队。长官，我从没听说过飞龙战队。

yingyinNormal.en: When the time comes, I will show her to the world and she will lead our army. "She"? Of course.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当时机成熟了，我会向世人揭示她的真实身份她会领导我们的军队。你是说她生了个女孩? 没错。

yingyinNormal.en: The people of the world look to us to lead. And we welcome that responsibility. We are heirs to a proud legacy of freedom.
yingyinNormal.zh: 世界人民关注着我们的领导力量，我们欢迎这样的责任心，我们是自由这一引以自豪遗产的继承人。

yingyinNormal.en: You will ride with our tumens and my sons. I name you commander of 1,000 men. But I lead this assault. You ride with the House of Kublai.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你将和我们的万夫团还有我的儿子们并驾齐驱，我任命你为千夫长，但是将由我来领导这次进攻，你和忽必烈军团一起走。

yingyinNormal.en: And if we take the steps that are necessary, if we're guided by the science, the facts, not fear, then I am absolutely confident that we can prevent a serious outbreak here in the United States and we can continue to lead the world in this urgent effort.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果我们采取必要的步骤，如果我们遵循科学，是事实，而不是恐惧，我特别充满信心，我们可以避免它在美国很严重地爆发，我们能够继续领导世界进行这一紧迫的努力。

yingyinNormal.en: Bury the lead, why don't you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 就该掐死在萌芽期，对吧？

yingyinNormal.en: All right, just follow my lead.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，跟着我的话锋转。

yingyinNormal.en: Will, I have a lead, but I need time.
yingyinNormal.zh: Will，有线索了，不过需要时间。

yingyinNormal.en: Be one with the blades. Lead their path.
yingyinNormal.zh: 用刀剑锋芒来指引道路

yingyinNormal.en: The last of which will lead you to the coin.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最后一个谜题将会带你们找到金币。

yingyinNormal.en: In the equations and logics that lead to reason.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有那些引导推理的方程式和逻辑。

yingyinNormal.en: The lead Secret Service man, he gave me the gun.
yingyinNormal.zh: 特勤局的主管，他把枪给了我

yingyinNormal.en: Nice motivational speech from our lead guitarist.
yingyinNormal.zh: 感谢主音吉他手激动人心的致辞。

yingyinNormal.en: No one enters Lake-town but by lead of the master.
yingyinNormal.zh: 除非城主带路，没有人进得了长湖城。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, that's Lead foot. They rip him apart. Savages.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是铅腿。他死得好惨。一群野蛮人。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adj. 最重要的
n. 领导者；领袖；领奏者；领唱者；报纸社论；空白段；顶枝；指向符；带头者；议会联络官
n. 领导；领导地位；领导人
adj. 使人产生误解的；导致错误印象的
v. 使产生错误想法；欺骗

word_family.mean: v. 带领（人）前进；牵着…前进；带领；率领；领先于；过；开始；让；组织

sense_info_list.en: to have sth as a result; to be the reason why sb does or thinks sth

examination_example.sentence: A series of fires and overcrowded conditions <highlight>led</highlight> to the construction of the existing Treasury Building.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一系列火灾和过度拥挤的条件导致了现有国库大楼的建造。

examination_example.sentence: Failing to recognize that, he notes, <highlight>leads</highlight> to "an overly simplified view of what the solutions might be.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他指出，如果没有认识到这一点，就会产生“对解决方案过于简单化的看法。”

examination_example.sentence: Americans buy roughly 20 billion garments a year and this excess <highlight>leads</highlight> to waste.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国人每年购买大约200亿件服装，这种过剩导致浪费。

sense_info_list.en: be in charge or command of

examination_example.sentence: We should press our government to <highlight>lead</highlight> the combat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们应该敦促我们的政府领导战斗。

examination_example.sentence: They could distort the achievement-based system of peer-review-<highlight>led</highlight> research.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们可能会扭曲以同行评审为导向、以学术成就基础的研究体系。

examination_example.sentence: peer-review-<highlight>led</highlight> research
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同行评审为导向的研究

sense_info_list.en: be the best at sth; to be in first place; the amount or distance that sb / sth is in front of sb / sth else

examination_example.sentence: France <highlight>leads</highlight> the charge on Digital Tax.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 法国率先征收数字税。

examination_example.sentence: California is <highlight>leading</highlight> the way, as it does on so many climate efforts, in figuring out the details.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 加州在解决细节方面走在了前面，就像它在许多气候问题上所做的那样。

examination_example.sentence: While the rest of the world takes the <highlight>lead</highlight>, the United States is also seeing a remarkable shift.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在世界其他国家领先的同时，美国也看到了一个显著的转变。

sense_info_list.en: to go with or in front of a person or an animal to show the way or to make them go in the right direction

examination_example.sentence: Trail blazes, tire tracks, and other features can <highlight>lead</highlight> you to civilization.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 开拓者，轮胎痕迹和其他特征可以引导你走向文明。

sense_info_list.en: go in a particular direction or to a particular place
have or experience a particular way of life
a piece of information that allows a discovery to be made or a solution to be found

n. 领导者；领袖；领奏者；领唱者；报纸社论；空白段；顶枝；指向符；带头者；议会联络官

sense_info_list.en: go in a particular direction or have a particular result, or to allow or cause this

examination_example.sentence: But what is yet to be demonstrated is whether the founder's passion <highlight>leads</highlight> to increased team performance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但还有待证明的是，创始人的激情是否会导致团队绩效的提高。

examination_example.sentence: It can <highlight>lead</highlight> to new discoveries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它可以带来新的发现。

examination_example.sentence: This preoccupation inevitably <highlight>leads</highlight> to an old debate: whether nature or nurture moulds us more.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种专注不可避免地引发了一场长久存在的辩论:是先天还是后天更能塑造我们。

sense_info_list.en: have the advantage over competitors in a race or game

examination_example.sentence: A range of factors has pushed Western Australia's desert to the <highlight>lead</highlight> of this automation revolution.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一系列因素促使西澳大利亚的沙漠成为这场自动化革命的领头羊。

examination_example.sentence: With the use of driverless vehicles seemingly inevitable, mining companies in the vast Australian desert state of Western Australia are definitely taking the <highlight>lead</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着无人驾驶汽车的使用似乎不可避免，位于澳大利亚广袤沙漠地带的西澳大利亚州的矿业公司无疑在这方面处于领先地位。

examination_example.sentence: Scottish councils are set to be the first with the power to levy charges on visitors, with Edinburgh likely to <highlight>lead</highlight> the way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 苏格兰议会将成为第一个有权向游客收费的地方，爱丁堡很可能会率先实施。

sense_info_list.en: control a group of people, a country, or a situation

examination_example.sentence: China's National Bureau of Statistics, China's State Council <highlight>Leading</highlight> Group Office of Poverty Alleviation and Development.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 中国国家统计局、国务院扶贫开发领导小组办公室。

examination_example.sentence: Several European capitals, including Paris and Berlin, are <highlight>leading</highlight> a campaign for tougher regulation by the European Union.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 包括巴黎和柏林在内的几个欧洲国家的首都，正在领导一场由欧盟实施更严格监督的运动。

examination_example.sentence: Teacher-<highlight>led</highlight> school activities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 教师领导的校园活动。

sense_info_list.en: be in charge or command of

examination_example.sentence: We want to <highlight>lead</highlight> the way in restoring the health of the ocean for future generations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们希望带头为子孙后代恢复海洋的健康。

sense_info_list.en: the main part or actor in a film or play

examination_example.sentence: Vas Taras, the <highlight>lead</highlight> author of the study, puts it this way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这项研究的主要作者Vas Taras是这样说的。

examination_example.sentence: The test results show that one of the products is mold-infested and the other product contains levels of <highlight>lead</highlight> that are too high.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 测试结果显示，其中一种产品长满了霉菌，另一种产品的含铅量过高。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adj. 最重要的
n. 领导者；领袖；领奏者；领唱者；报纸社论；空白段；顶枝；指向符；带头者；议会联络官
n. 领导；领导地位；领导人
adj. 使人产生误解的；导致错误印象的

examination_example.sentence: A bridge with big, light-blue loops <highlight>leads</highlight> into the business district. In the center of the main road, there's a long line of flags of the world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一座带有巨大浅蓝色圆环的大桥通往商业区。在主干道的中央，有一长列世界各国的国旗。

sense_info_list.en: control a group of people; a country; or a situation

examination_example.sentence: It has <highlight>led</highlight> some other companies to follow suit.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它已经导致其他一些公司的效仿。

examination_example.sentence: Mothering Justice, <highlight>led</highlight> by women of color, went last year to lobby on issues that affect working mothers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 由有色人种女性领导的“母亲正义”(Mothering Justice)去年就影响职场母亲的问题进行了游说。

examination_example.sentence: Those assumptions <highlight>lead</highlight> us to the perception that people in poverty are lazy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些假设使我们认为穷人是懒惰的。

sense_info_list.en: be in charge or command of

examination_example.sentence: She <highlight>led</highlight> me past row after row of books, to a corner of the library.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她领着我经过一排又一排的书，来到图书馆的一个角落。

examination_example.sentence: Wilson Wong will <highlight>lead</highlight> a class of rising fifth-graders at a day camp dedicated to Chinese culture.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Wilson Wong将带领一群即将升入五年级的学生参加一个以中国文化为主题的日间夏令营。

sense_info_list.en: the main part or actor in a film or play

examination_example.sentence: Utrecht University sociologist Arnout van de Rijt was the <highlight>lead</highlight> author on the 2018 paper showing the rich get richer.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 乌得勒支大学的社会学家Arnout van de Rijt是2018年那篇揭示富人变得更富的论文的主要作者。

examination_example.sentence: "We thought we would see differences based on the housing types." said the <highlight>lead</highlight> author of the study, Julie Robinson.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该研究的主要作者(Julie Robinson)说：“我们认为，根据住房类型，我们会看到其中的差异。”

sense_info_list.en: have the advantage over competitors in a race or game

examination_example.sentence: Glasgow has pledged to take the <highlight>lead</highlight> in reducing carbon emissions in the UK.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 格拉斯哥已承诺在英国率先减少碳排放。

examination_example.sentence: I nearly tripped over someone's computer electrical <highlight>lead</highlight> the other day in my local café.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 前几天在我当地的咖啡馆里，我差点被别人的电脑电线绊倒。

sense_info_list.en: a piece of information that allows a discovery to be made or a solution to be found
an example or action for people to copy

word_usage.usage: lead作名词，表“首位，领先”解时，常与定冠词the连用；作“领导，榜样”时，常与不定冠词a连用；作“线索”解时，常用复数形式。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指为某人指方向，但自己不一定亲自引路，也可表示指导一群人的事或活动。
普通用词，可与 conduct 换用，指引导者与被引导者双方彼此合作，共同努力的关系。
指走在前面给某人引路或带路人共同去达到某一目标。用于抽象意义时，指在某项活动或运动中起主导和组织作用。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adj. 最重要的
n. 领导者；领袖；领奏者；领唱者；报纸社论；空白段；顶枝；指向符；带头者；议会联络官
n. 领导；领导地位；领导人
v. 使产生错误想法；欺骗

word_family.mean: v. 带领（人）前进；牵着…前进；带领；率领；领先于；过；开始；让；组织

sense_info_list.en: control a group of people, a country, or a situation

examination_example.sentence: According to Paragraph 5, hypnosis works by <highlight>leading</highlight> patients' consciousness away from reality.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据第5段，催眠的工作原理是引导病人的意识远离现实。

examination_example.sentence: Note also the facts important for your purpose as well as anything which <highlight>leads</highlight> you to further research.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 还要注意对你的目的很重要的事实，以及任何引导你进一步研究的东西。

examination_example.sentence: It has <highlight>led</highlight> me to where I am today.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它指引我走到了今天。

examination_example.sentence: It is easier to avoid a discussion, but risking talking about it may eventually <highlight>lead</highlight> to a better outcome.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 避免讨论更容易，但冒险讨论可能最终会导致更好的结果。

examination_example.sentence: This, of course, can <highlight>lead</highlight> to less pain.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当然，这可以导致更少的痛苦。

examination_example.sentence: This may be because more life experience usually <highlight>leads</highlight> to more defined priorities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这可能是因为更多的生活经历通常会导致更明确的优先事项。

examination_example.sentence: I don't know where it will <highlight>lead</highlight>, but I'm excited I'm on this pursuit.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我不知道它将要通向哪里，但我很兴奋我在追求这个目标。

examination_example.sentence: That movie <highlight>led</highlight> him into the second half of his career.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这部电影让他进入了职业生涯的后半段。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2018-2021年4年间全国各省市中考试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adj. 最重要的
n. 领导者；领袖；领奏者；领唱者；报纸社论；空白段；顶枝；指向符；带头者；议会联络官
n. 领导；领导地位；领导人
v. 使产生错误想法；欺骗

word_family.mean: v. 带领（人）前进；牵着…前进；带领；率领；领先于；过；开始；让；组织

sense_info_list.en: to have something as a result

examination_example.sentence: Eating too much ice cream may <highlight>lead</highlight> to stomach problems.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 吃太多冰淇淋可能会引起胃病。

examination_example.sentence: Extreme weather <highlight>led</highlight> to wildfires burning in Europe.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 极端天气导致欧洲野火燃烧。

examination_example.sentence: For Harvey, it was losing his job that <highlight>led</highlight> to him becoming homeless.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对哈维来说，正是失业导致他无家可归。

sense_info_list.en: to be in control of something; to be the leader of something

examination_example.sentence: Mr. Bryant helped <highlight>lead</highlight> the US Olympic team to win the gold medal in 2008 and 2012.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 布莱恩特先生曾在2008年和2012年帮助带领美国奥运代表队夺得金牌。

examination_example.sentence: Marchenko prepared to <highlight>lead</highlight> his students out onto the ice.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Marchenko准备把他的学生带到冰上。

examination_example.sentence: What can <highlight>lead</highlight> you to success?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 什么能引领你走向成功？

sense_info_list.en: to go with or in front of a person or an animal to show the way or to make them go in the right direction

examination_example.sentence: Ask grown-ups to <highlight>lead</highlight> them to bed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 请大人领他们上床睡觉。

examination_example.sentence: He asked some soldiers to <highlight>lead</highlight> the elephant onto a boat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他让一些士兵把大象带到船上。

examination_example.sentence: Then he <highlight>led</highlight> Alex into another area of the zoo.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然后他把亚历克斯领到动物园的另一个区域。

sense_info_list.en: have or experience a particular way of life

examination_example.sentence: If we try our best to improve these life skills, we will <highlight>lead</highlight> a happier, and healthier life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果我们尽力改善这些生活技能，我们将过上更快乐、更健康的生活。

examination_example.sentence: In fact, good students may just end up doing jobs they don't like, and some even <highlight>lead</highlight> an unhappy life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，好学生最终可能只是做他们不喜欢的工作，有些甚至过着不快乐的生活。

examination_example.sentence: Thanks to the government, many poor families in the countryside are <highlight>leading</highlight> a better life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 多亏了政府，农村的许多贫困家庭过上了更好的生活。

sense_info_list.en: the chief part in a play or film

examination_example.sentence: "Seeing one's friends have similar behaviors will reinforce (强化) one's own values, opinions, and interests," <highlight>lead</highlight> scientist Carolyn Parkinson told Business Insider.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “看到自己的朋友有类似的行为会强化自己的价值观、观点和兴趣。”首席科学家卡罗琳·帕金森告诉《商业内幕》。

examination_example.sentence: "We believe these color patterns are the result of small changes in blood flow triggered (触发) by the central nervous (神经) system," <highlight>lead</highlight> researcher Alex Martinez said.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “我们认为这些脸色模式源于中枢神经系统触发血流的细微变化。”首席研究员亚历克斯·马丁内斯说。

examination_example.sentence: John McGeehan, one of the <highlight>lead</highlight> researchers, said, "We've made an improved enzyme. It's better than the natural one."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首席研究员之一约翰·麦吉汉说:“我们已经制造了一种改良的酶。它比天然的酶要好。”

sense_info_list.en: have the advantage over competitors in a race or game

examination_example.sentence: Putting in more effort, Eddie reached Riley and then suddenly he was in the <highlight>lead</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Eddie更加努力，赶上了Riley，然后他突然领先了。

examination_example.sentence: Chinese companies <highlight>lead</highlight> in global 5G patent applications（专利应用） with Huawei taking the crown, according to a report by IPlytics, an authorized patent data company．
examination_example.sentence_trans: 授权专利数据公司IPlytics的一份报告显示，中国企业在全球5G专利申请中处于领先地位，华为摘得桂冠。

examination_example.sentence: Chinese companies <highlight>lead</highlight> the 5G patent race．
examination_example.sentence_trans: 中国企业引领5G专利竞赛。

sense_info_list.en: to go in a particular direction or to a particular place

examination_example.sentence: I saw a path <highlight>leading</highlight> into some woods.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我看到一条通往树林的小路。

examination_example.sentence: The QR code <highlight>leads</highlight> to an e-book app, on which the passengers can read the e-book for free.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 二维码通向一个电子书应用程序，乘客可以在上面免费阅读电子书。

examination_example.sentence: Each hole <highlight>leads</highlight> to a small tube that runs to your nose.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每个洞都通向一根小管子，这条管子通向你的鼻子。

word_usage.usage: lead作名词，表“首位，领先”解时，常与定冠词the连用；作“领导，榜样”时，常与不定冠词a连用；作“线索”解时，常用复数形式。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指为某人指方向，但自己不一定亲自引路，也可表示指导一群人的事或活动。
指带领某人至某处，也指为某人或某物引路，引申则指引导某人的行为或观点。
指走在前面给某人引路或带路人共同去达到某一目标。用于抽象意义时，指在某项活动或运动中起主导和组织作用。
